<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('./partials/head') -%>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>URL Shortener API</h1>
      <p>Created by <a href="https://autumnbullard-portfolio.herokuapp.com" target="_blank">Autumn Bullard</a> &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear(); %></p>
    </header>
    <main>
      <p>An API that takes a submitted URL and creates an alias URL that, if navigated to, will redirect to the original URL.</p>
      <p>View the <a href="https://github.com/autumnchris/url-shortener-api" target="_blank">source code</a> for this project.</p>
      <hr>
      <section>
        <h2>Project Usage</h2>
        <p>Submit a web address in the form below to get a generated alias URL that will be used to redirect to the original URL.</p>
        <p>For example, if I wanted an alias URL that will redirect to GitHub's homepage I would enter <code>https://github.com</code> into the input field and upon submission I would receive a new URL as my alias that I can now use to redirect to the original URL.</p>
        <form action="/api/shorturl/new" method="post">
          <div class="form-group">
            <input type="text" name="url" placeholder="Enter a URL to be shortened" aria-label="Enter a URL to be shortened" required>
          </div>
          <input type="submit" class="button" value="Submit">
        </form>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
